1
00:00:00,349 --> 00:00:02,301
After last week's recording,

2
00:00:02,726 --> 00:00:05,223
I wondered if I should
go buy a lie detector.

3
00:00:05,248 --> 00:00:08,091
- It's a great way to get
close to people. - I know.

4
00:00:09,851 --> 00:00:14,304
Is there someone who's making it
obvious that they're interested in you?

5
00:00:14,544 --> 00:00:15,544
There's no one.

6
00:00:15,569 --> 00:00:18,872
- The second one with the best impression?
- It's Ji-min.

7
00:00:19,170 --> 00:00:21,582
I feel so bad for Yang Ji-min.

8
00:00:21,607 --> 00:00:27,349
She keeps lingering around Ahn Ji-min, but
she can't proactively express her feelings.

9
00:00:27,374 --> 00:00:30,274
She has no chance to,
so I found that regrettable.

10
00:00:30,770 --> 00:00:33,496
I was really shocked at
the end when Jung-woo

11
00:00:33,521 --> 00:00:36,009
was choosing who to
give his Love Coin to.

12
00:00:36,034 --> 00:00:37,211
Yeah, it was surprising.

13
00:00:37,236 --> 00:00:42,905
In the beginning, Jung-woo and In-seong
were like the official couple of the show.

14
00:00:43,378 --> 00:00:45,124
And it felt like they broke up.

15
00:00:45,309 --> 00:00:48,301
Also there was Su-won and Ha-neul.

16
00:00:48,326 --> 00:00:50,700
There's a strange tension between them.

17
00:00:50,725 --> 00:00:52,543
- Right.
- Yes.

18
00:00:52,705 --> 00:00:55,388
So I can't predict what
will happen to them.

19
00:00:55,413 --> 00:00:59,794
As third-party observers,
we can see who likes who,

20
00:00:59,819 --> 00:01:04,031
but it seems like they're
not able to really tell.

21
00:01:04,377 --> 00:01:06,535
All right, so there's a
question we must solve today.

22
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:09,719
We can't just relax and watch today.

23
00:01:09,744 --> 00:01:12,929
We must keep a sharp eye on them.

24
00:01:12,954 --> 00:01:14,893
Shall we check the question first?

25
00:01:16,617 --> 00:01:21,811
(Today's Question: Who gave
Love Coins to each other?)

26
00:01:21,836 --> 00:01:25,069
Can we answer that now?
I'm super confident.

27
00:01:25,094 --> 00:01:27,231
There must be a trap then. Right?

28
00:01:27,256 --> 00:01:28,868
Yes, I think we need to watch it first.

29
00:01:28,893 --> 00:01:30,760
Let's watch the video first.

30
00:01:32,293 --> 00:01:35,407
(Autumn rain is falling on the morning
of the fourth day at the Love Mansion.)

31
00:01:35,432 --> 00:01:37,035
It's already the fourth morning.

32
00:01:37,697 --> 00:01:38,935
What time is it?

33
00:01:39,735 --> 00:01:42,485
It was around 7:40 when I
came back from working out.

34
00:01:42,510 --> 00:01:43,836
What? Really?

35
00:01:44,338 --> 00:01:46,538
I think it's about 8 o'clock now.

36
00:01:47,834 --> 00:01:50,215
Don't you have to go? By 8?

37
00:01:50,478 --> 00:01:52,932
- 8:30.
- 8:30?

38
00:01:52,957 --> 00:01:53,957
Yes.

39
00:01:54,183 --> 00:01:56,159
You're going to get all
ready before leaving?

40
00:01:56,184 --> 00:01:57,184
Yes.

41
00:01:57,391 --> 00:01:59,638
- Is she going to school?
- Does she have plans?

42
00:02:01,556 --> 00:02:03,603
- It must be an important day.
- Yeah.

43
00:02:04,257 --> 00:02:06,019
Do we have to decide who makes breakfast?

44
00:02:06,044 --> 00:02:07,805
Everyone ate breakfast this morning.

45
00:02:08,431 --> 00:02:10,872
Then how about Ji-min and
Ji-min prepare breakfast tomorrow?

46
00:02:12,289 --> 00:02:15,670
- Whose idea was that? Yeo-min.
- Yeo-min played Cupid.

47
00:02:16,079 --> 00:02:18,634
Then how about Ji-min and
Ji-min prepare breakfast tomorrow?

48
00:02:18,659 --> 00:02:20,962
I can do it. I'll try making seaweed soup.

49
00:02:21,465 --> 00:02:24,784
- Do you know how to make it?
- I'll faithfully look it up.

50
00:02:25,582 --> 00:02:27,613
Oh, that's why she's getting ready?

51
00:02:27,638 --> 00:02:29,535
I thought she was going somewhere.

52
00:02:33,933 --> 00:02:36,248
(She almost fell trying to rush there.)

53
00:02:36,273 --> 00:02:38,798
- Oh my goodness!
- She must be nervous.

54
00:02:42,334 --> 00:02:44,876
(Ahn Ji-min arrived first.)

55
00:02:48,326 --> 00:02:49,732
(Rush)

56
00:02:50,661 --> 00:02:52,160
- Hello.
- Hello.

57
00:02:53,204 --> 00:02:54,783
- Hello.
- Hello.

58
00:02:55,733 --> 00:02:58,449
- Did you sleep well? - I just
learned the recipe for seaweed soup.

59
00:02:58,474 --> 00:02:59,474
Really?

60
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:02,060
She can't stop smiling.

61
00:03:03,414 --> 00:03:05,674
(Hehe)

62
00:03:10,165 --> 00:03:11,705
She keeps following him.

63
00:03:14,266 --> 00:03:16,639
- It's my first time making seaweed soup.
- Same here.

64
00:03:17,476 --> 00:03:19,214
I've seen my mom make it a lot.

65
00:03:19,524 --> 00:03:21,016
- Really?
- Yes.

66
00:03:21,408 --> 00:03:22,852
Sesame oil.

67
00:03:24,110 --> 00:03:27,706
Sesame oil.

68
00:03:30,902 --> 00:03:34,886
Do you know where the sesame oil is?

69
00:03:38,403 --> 00:03:39,803
It's really not here.

70
00:03:42,033 --> 00:03:43,858
It said we need sesame oil though.

71
00:03:45,076 --> 00:03:47,013
Da-Na said we shouldn't add sesame oil.

72
00:03:47,793 --> 00:03:49,439
- Why not?
- She said it's not that good.

73
00:03:50,789 --> 00:03:52,907
He asked Da-Na...

74
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:57,654
Once the seaweed expands...

75
00:03:57,679 --> 00:04:00,225
But won't it taste better
with the sesame oil?

76
00:04:00,896 --> 00:04:02,029
Should we add it?

77
00:04:02,372 --> 00:04:04,175
Does Da-Na not like sesame oil?

78
00:04:05,206 --> 00:04:06,524
I should've asked her.

79
00:04:07,736 --> 00:04:09,514
I can't find the sesame oil anyway.

80
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,008
- Really?
- Yes.

81
00:04:11,033 --> 00:04:13,708
Let's just use this
since we don't have that.

82
00:04:14,648 --> 00:04:16,600
Aren't you supposed to use sesame oil?

83
00:04:16,625 --> 00:04:18,816
Right. You're supposed to
stir-fry the seaweed with it.

84
00:04:18,841 --> 00:04:22,184
I would've insisted we use it.
I want to just pour the whole thing.

85
00:04:23,108 --> 00:04:25,608
- She even learned the recipe beforehand.
- I know.

86
00:04:29,617 --> 00:04:31,267
- The sesame oil.
- He found it!

87
00:04:32,531 --> 00:04:37,524
We have it. It'd be perfect if we
stir-fried the seaweed with that.

88
00:04:38,020 --> 00:04:39,020
Will he add it?

89
00:04:40,317 --> 00:04:42,697
- He's adding it.
- He was going to do it anyway!

90
00:04:47,679 --> 00:04:48,875
(Smile)

91
00:04:50,428 --> 00:04:51,428
She's adorable!

92
00:04:52,936 --> 00:04:54,906
- Come have breakfast.
- Okay.

93
00:04:56,489 --> 00:04:59,028
- We did a great job, right?
- Yes.

94
00:04:59,390 --> 00:05:01,786
It feels like...

95
00:05:03,695 --> 00:05:04,695
What's wrong?

96
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,696
It feels like the housewarming
party of newlyweds.

97
00:05:06,722 --> 00:05:07,810
Newlyweds?

98
00:05:08,962 --> 00:05:11,177
- Nice comment.
- Go, Yeo-min!

99
00:05:11,696 --> 00:05:13,482
Just act crazy and call him honey.

100
00:05:20,229 --> 00:05:21,429
This is delicious.

101
00:05:21,454 --> 00:05:22,633
- Is it good?
- Yup.

102
00:05:23,318 --> 00:05:24,421
(Push)

103
00:05:26,295 --> 00:05:28,361
(Ji-min takes good care of him.)

104
00:05:29,230 --> 00:05:31,857
Oh my goodness. Can't
they just get together?

105
00:05:32,801 --> 00:05:35,803
(Breakfast is over.)

106
00:05:37,207 --> 00:05:39,079
Did you have a good
time yesterday, Jung-woo?

107
00:05:39,722 --> 00:05:41,462
- Huh?
- Did you have fun?

108
00:05:41,487 --> 00:05:42,487
Did you?

109
00:05:44,961 --> 00:05:46,094
He's taken aback.

110
00:05:48,488 --> 00:05:49,488
I'm thirsty.

111
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:53,293
(Jung-woo is keeping
his lips sealed.)

112
00:05:53,723 --> 00:05:56,041
- He's thirsty.
- There's no cup.

113
00:05:56,870 --> 00:05:58,743
He's unable to give an answer.

114
00:05:59,301 --> 00:06:00,912
(Trying to remain cool)

115
00:06:02,565 --> 00:06:04,343
He has so many people to be conscious of.

116
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:06,560
(Bothered)

117
00:06:09,448 --> 00:06:10,956
How was your date?

118
00:06:12,615 --> 00:06:14,307
She's asking him right away again.

119
00:06:15,105 --> 00:06:16,920
It felt like a short break.

120
00:06:16,945 --> 00:06:20,980
But it did feel nice to see the
night view after a long time.

121
00:06:21,401 --> 00:06:22,401
(Nod)

122
00:06:24,630 --> 00:06:26,392
The streetlamps were beautiful.

123
00:06:26,417 --> 00:06:27,511
I'm jealous.

124
00:06:29,276 --> 00:06:30,832
I'm jealous.

125
00:06:32,056 --> 00:06:34,722
- Oh dear. - Gosh, he must
feel really uncomfortable.

126
00:06:37,075 --> 00:06:40,192
(The rain keeps falling without a care.)

127
00:06:41,295 --> 00:06:45,020
(What's today's challenge?)

128
00:06:46,391 --> 00:06:49,177
It's the first time they're leaving
Love Mansion together, right?

129
00:06:49,202 --> 00:06:50,838
- Oh my.
- You're right.

130
00:06:51,143 --> 00:06:53,031
There are so many great places in Seoul.

131
00:06:53,056 --> 00:06:55,477
(What kind of rhythm will
they go along with today?)

132
00:06:56,910 --> 00:06:58,672
What did you guys talk about last night?

133
00:06:58,784 --> 00:07:02,310
I heard you guys have
a feeling who likes who.

134
00:07:02,559 --> 00:07:06,051
Like you guys figured out
who has an interest in who.

135
00:07:06,221 --> 00:07:07,221
Tell me, too.

136
00:07:07,466 --> 00:07:09,915
- I was drunk, so I don't remember?
- Gosh!

137
00:07:09,940 --> 00:07:11,582
I'm the only one in the dark!

138
00:07:11,607 --> 00:07:13,164
You had a fun date instead!

139
00:07:13,571 --> 00:07:15,309
I'm curious about this though.

140
00:07:16,098 --> 00:07:18,582
How about we play the Truth Game?

141
00:07:19,942 --> 00:07:21,696
- Here?
- Great idea.

142
00:07:22,201 --> 00:07:23,345
- Sure.
- Right now?

143
00:07:23,370 --> 00:07:25,473
Just simple questions.
It'll be like a mini game.

144
00:07:25,498 --> 00:07:27,569
Okay, as long as the
questions aren't too difficult.

145
00:07:27,594 --> 00:07:29,927
- We'll just go with easy ones.
- Yeah.

146
00:07:30,765 --> 00:07:32,058
You go first, Ha-neul.

147
00:07:32,083 --> 00:07:35,322
You know how we put our
Love Coin in someone's locker?

148
00:07:35,953 --> 00:07:38,492
Did you put it somewhere else,
or are you going to do that now?

149
00:07:39,076 --> 00:07:40,520
I'm really confused right now.

150
00:07:41,864 --> 00:07:43,531
Right, that's inevitable.

151
00:07:44,336 --> 00:07:46,788
At first, I was sure of who
to pick but not anymore.

152
00:07:47,943 --> 00:07:48,943
What about you?

153
00:07:49,665 --> 00:07:51,625
I think it might change today.

154
00:07:51,947 --> 00:07:53,645
Right? Challenges have an influence.

155
00:07:53,670 --> 00:07:57,901
Whoever I do it with, I think there's
a possibility my feelings will change.

156
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:02,344
What's this? Is he indirectly telling her?

157
00:08:02,369 --> 00:08:05,339
- That's possible. - It seems like
it's directed towards In-seong, right?

158
00:08:05,364 --> 00:08:06,364
Yup.

159
00:08:06,389 --> 00:08:08,310
Ha-neul, did you put
the coin somewhere else?

160
00:08:10,403 --> 00:08:11,403
No, I didn't.

161
00:08:12,087 --> 00:08:15,150
- Really?
- I thought about it a lot,

162
00:08:15,175 --> 00:08:17,447
but I have no clue how I
feel, so I just left it there.

163
00:08:17,657 --> 00:08:19,688
Even after going on a date with just him?

164
00:08:20,516 --> 00:08:26,357
Right now, I'm wondering if I
can give my heart to someone.

165
00:08:27,046 --> 00:08:28,832
- She's careful.
- I see.

166
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:32,939
Maybe it could change?

167
00:08:34,571 --> 00:08:35,771
Is it my turn now?

168
00:08:35,983 --> 00:08:39,271
I'm not talking about right now, but
when the nine of us met for the first time.

169
00:08:39,296 --> 00:08:41,361
Who was the second
person you got interested in?

170
00:08:44,884 --> 00:08:49,026
For me, it was Ji-min.

171
00:08:53,667 --> 00:08:55,836
Ji-min, you need to
be a bit more proactive.

172
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,433
(Nod)

173
00:08:57,831 --> 00:09:01,547
You haven't been straightforward.

174
00:09:01,830 --> 00:09:04,147
But do others need to know?
Only she needs to know.

175
00:09:04,396 --> 00:09:07,070
But Yeo-min is frustrated
because the girl doesn't know either.

176
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:12,281
Even she has no idea how you feel
because you're not expressing yourself.

177
00:09:13,463 --> 00:09:16,327
You can't be passive about this.
It's hopeless then.

178
00:09:16,663 --> 00:09:18,130
Nothing will work out.

179
00:09:20,263 --> 00:09:25,183
I'm trying to subtly take care of
the people I want to get to know.

180
00:09:26,245 --> 00:09:27,967
I talked with Ha-neul a lot yesterday.

181
00:09:28,817 --> 00:09:29,864
(Ha-neul?)

182
00:09:29,889 --> 00:09:32,811
We were tired, so we both
slept on the bed yesterday.

183
00:09:33,251 --> 00:09:35,052
(He's bringing that up?)

184
00:09:35,231 --> 00:09:39,010
When you see them in the video,
you can tell nothing happened.

185
00:09:39,436 --> 00:09:41,615
They really slept on the
bed because they were tired.

186
00:09:42,028 --> 00:09:44,840
He just had to mention the word "bed."

187
00:09:44,967 --> 00:09:46,922
He's kind of provoking Su-won.

188
00:09:47,783 --> 00:09:50,592
(Uncomfortable)

189
00:09:50,961 --> 00:09:52,072
But I'm curious.

190
00:09:52,461 --> 00:09:56,360
- You said that you know how you feel.
- Yeah.

191
00:09:57,286 --> 00:09:59,833
Doesn't everyone know
that? I was pretty blunt.

192
00:09:59,858 --> 00:10:03,257
Do you think she's interested in you, too?

193
00:10:04,132 --> 00:10:06,355
(Curious)

194
00:10:07,010 --> 00:10:08,010
Well...

195
00:10:08,876 --> 00:10:11,495
- I think so.
- That's good then.

196
00:10:12,118 --> 00:10:13,197
That's what's important.

197
00:10:13,222 --> 00:10:17,639
Even if she isn't, I'm the type to
keep trying to win her heart if I like her.

198
00:10:21,859 --> 00:10:25,459
(The two have different
styles when it comes to love.)

199
00:10:25,971 --> 00:10:29,538
(Finally, they arrive at the location
where the challenge will take place.)

200
00:10:29,563 --> 00:10:30,963
Are we dancing today?

201
00:10:31,890 --> 00:10:33,325
I think it'll be fun.

202
00:10:34,590 --> 00:10:37,265
(A place that's filled with jazz music)

203
00:10:38,278 --> 00:10:39,544
Where are they?

204
00:10:39,682 --> 00:10:40,682
What's going on?

205
00:10:42,132 --> 00:10:44,740
(Why are they surprised?)

206
00:10:49,644 --> 00:10:53,862
(In front of them is the most
honest and hot language: dance)

207
00:10:55,604 --> 00:10:57,413
Seriously. What do we do?

208
00:11:04,670 --> 00:11:06,638
I was really surprised.

209
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:09,928
I realized today wasn't
going to be an easy day either.

210
00:11:11,176 --> 00:11:14,289
- There's a high possibility Yeo-min
will be the best here. - Right.

211
00:11:16,445 --> 00:11:17,944
It's going to be hard to win today.

212
00:11:17,969 --> 00:11:19,873
(Worried)

213
00:11:20,453 --> 00:11:22,131
(That's so cool!)

214
00:11:26,819 --> 00:11:28,247
That was awesome!

215
00:11:28,272 --> 00:11:29,558
(Cheering)

216
00:11:29,712 --> 00:11:31,863
- Hello.
- Hello.

217
00:11:32,349 --> 00:11:34,715
You all came to the right place.

218
00:11:36,436 --> 00:11:41,032
I'm Park Ji-eun, the dance coach who will
be in charge of the couple dance challenge.

219
00:11:41,297 --> 00:11:43,906
(Cheer)

220
00:11:44,316 --> 00:11:47,403
These are professional dancers
Kim Soo-ro and Lee Hae-in.

221
00:11:48,399 --> 00:11:49,804
It's nice to meet you.

222
00:11:49,829 --> 00:11:56,334
Today's couple challenge is
"blind choice couple dance."

223
00:11:59,670 --> 00:12:01,410
- "Blind choice."
- What's that?

224
00:12:03,654 --> 00:12:06,956
You will choose your
partner without looking.

225
00:12:07,293 --> 00:12:10,689
You just saw their dance, right?

226
00:12:10,908 --> 00:12:16,225
That's the choreography
you will have to perform today.

227
00:12:16,682 --> 00:12:18,087
(Oh my god.)

228
00:12:20,577 --> 00:12:22,310
(Everyone is taken aback.)

229
00:12:22,335 --> 00:12:24,443
- It's too hard!
- They have to learn it in one day?

230
00:12:24,468 --> 00:12:26,278
Oh no. It's difficult!

231
00:12:26,764 --> 00:12:28,408
We have to do that? No way.

232
00:12:28,433 --> 00:12:30,346
How do we do that?

233
00:12:30,664 --> 00:12:31,664
I'm doomed.

234
00:12:32,084 --> 00:12:35,382
As a dancer, I'm confident.

235
00:12:35,679 --> 00:12:36,812
I think I'll win.

236
00:12:37,737 --> 00:12:41,365
The key point is to not let
go of each other's hands.

237
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:44,012
My goodness.

238
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:50,627
You must communicate with your partners
and focus on them as much as possible.

239
00:12:50,652 --> 00:12:53,887
- I'll have to give it my all.
- Whoa. Are you confident?

240
00:12:53,912 --> 00:12:55,512
Nope. I'm just doing it.

241
00:12:56,781 --> 00:12:58,392
I'll just have to go through with it.

242
00:12:59,777 --> 00:13:03,205
You will now choose your dance partner.

243
00:13:04,170 --> 00:13:06,694
(Blind Choice: They will
cover their eyes with the

244
00:13:06,719 --> 00:13:09,489
blindfold and choose their
partner by touching their hands.)

245
00:13:10,129 --> 00:13:11,748
Gosh, I just got goosebumps.

246
00:13:11,773 --> 00:13:13,439
Are you coming down with something?

247
00:13:14,406 --> 00:13:16,203
Should we turn on the heater?

248
00:13:16,850 --> 00:13:21,286
The female participants
can choose the blindfolds.

249
00:13:21,311 --> 00:13:24,481
- So this is how the couples are chosen?
- I guess the girls are wearing them.

250
00:13:24,506 --> 00:13:27,611
(With nervousness, they decide
the order of the blind choice.)

251
00:13:28,235 --> 00:13:29,925
- No. 4.
- You're No. 4.

252
00:13:30,332 --> 00:13:33,253
- Why is there a number?
- I think it's for the order they'll go in.

253
00:13:33,602 --> 00:13:35,192
So there's an order.

254
00:13:35,496 --> 00:13:37,694
- I got number 2.
- You're No. 2.

255
00:13:37,719 --> 00:13:38,719
She's No. 3.

256
00:13:39,823 --> 00:13:41,270
She's No. 1.

257
00:13:41,908 --> 00:13:44,027
- I'm No. 5.
- All right.

258
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:51,239
You will put the blindfold on and find
the partner you want to dance with.

259
00:13:51,264 --> 00:13:54,958
You can only touch their
hands and not anywhere else.

260
00:13:58,450 --> 00:13:59,450
Oh my gosh!

261
00:14:00,910 --> 00:14:02,531
Please put your blindfold on.

262
00:14:04,353 --> 00:14:05,819
Wow, we get to watch?

263
00:14:06,108 --> 00:14:08,005
For some reason, I'm nervous.

264
00:14:08,340 --> 00:14:09,340
I know.

265
00:14:09,761 --> 00:14:13,524
Okay, the first person wore her blindfold.

266
00:14:14,483 --> 00:14:17,244
Can the men switch spots?

267
00:14:18,677 --> 00:14:20,915
Just switch comfortably.

268
00:14:21,553 --> 00:14:23,332
Before you choose your partner,

269
00:14:23,442 --> 00:14:26,754
while you're holding his hands, you
should carefully make your decision by

270
00:14:26,779 --> 00:14:30,002
observing how they feel and what
kind of teamwork you can have with them.

271
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:35,063
All right. We will now begin the selection.

272
00:14:37,543 --> 00:14:40,677
(Who will Ha-neul, who
is going first, choose?)

273
00:14:43,156 --> 00:14:47,997
I hoped that Ha-neul would
approach me and choose me.

274
00:14:48,335 --> 00:14:51,011
- Won't he squeeze her hand?
- I think he'll give her a signal.

275
00:14:51,036 --> 00:14:54,146
- Yes, I think so!
- "It's me."

276
00:14:54,747 --> 00:14:55,747
Oh my god!

277
00:14:55,772 --> 00:14:58,653
(She carefully moves step by step.)

278
00:15:00,024 --> 00:15:03,793
(The men are nervously watching her.)

279
00:15:06,498 --> 00:15:07,982
Please stretch out your hands.

280
00:15:09,612 --> 00:15:12,502
- Gosh, what do we do?
- They must be nervous.

281
00:15:15,189 --> 00:15:16,760
(Embarrassed)

282
00:15:17,886 --> 00:15:19,117
(Shy)

283
00:15:21,797 --> 00:15:25,260
(The ones watching them
feel ticklish emotions.)

284
00:15:28,063 --> 00:15:31,306
(With the blindfold on, the senses
of the tips of her fingers heighten.)

285
00:15:33,996 --> 00:15:38,575
I think they'll both feel
nervous and excited.

286
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,833
Look at Da-Na.

287
00:15:42,192 --> 00:15:45,098
(Oh my god. I'm getting all excited!)

288
00:15:46,039 --> 00:15:51,128
It's not easy to find the partner
you want just by holding their hands.

289
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:55,023
Why is Jae-hyung's expression so cute?

290
00:15:57,255 --> 00:15:59,193
(Vague)

291
00:16:03,657 --> 00:16:04,657
(Startled)

292
00:16:05,982 --> 00:16:06,982
(Reach)

293
00:16:07,007 --> 00:16:08,848
(Ha-neul was surprised
because Su-won reached

294
00:16:08,873 --> 00:16:10,672
out first and his hand
brushed against hers.)

295
00:16:11,542 --> 00:16:12,795
He squeezed her hand!

296
00:16:13,869 --> 00:16:15,003
This is hilarious!

297
00:16:17,656 --> 00:16:20,373
(Su-won is tightly grabbing her hands.)

298
00:16:21,514 --> 00:16:24,425
(Did she notice his signal?)

299
00:16:25,725 --> 00:16:27,009
(Squeeze)

300
00:16:27,725 --> 00:16:29,668
(Stare)

301
00:16:30,452 --> 00:16:33,515
Am I not allowed to go
back once I pass by them?

302
00:16:34,201 --> 00:16:35,368
(Did she...?!)

303
00:16:35,393 --> 00:16:38,902
No, you can think carefully
and come to a decision.

304
00:16:40,018 --> 00:16:42,906
(She holds his hands one more time.)

305
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:45,633
Will she go to the next person?

306
00:16:47,038 --> 00:16:48,547
Or will she just choose him?

307
00:16:51,686 --> 00:16:56,530
- You choose him?
- Yes.

308
00:16:57,158 --> 00:16:58,852
(it worked!)

309
00:16:58,877 --> 00:17:01,010
She didn't even go to Ji-min.

310
00:17:01,326 --> 00:17:05,364
Then please hold his hand
and take off your blindfold.

311
00:17:06,638 --> 00:17:08,154
I got goosebumps!

312
00:17:14,346 --> 00:17:15,346
(Blush)

313
00:17:16,311 --> 00:17:19,751
(The first couple is Su-won and Ha-neul.)

314
00:17:20,349 --> 00:17:22,826
- My face is red.
- Please go on the stage.

315
00:17:24,046 --> 00:17:27,709
She made her choice without
going all the way to the end.

316
00:17:28,170 --> 00:17:29,447
My hands were sweaty.

317
00:17:32,476 --> 00:17:33,666
Way to go!

318
00:17:34,629 --> 00:17:35,696
The second person.

319
00:17:40,287 --> 00:17:42,509
I wanted to be with Ji-min.

320
00:17:46,886 --> 00:17:49,857
(His hands are the first ones she touches.)

321
00:17:51,481 --> 00:17:54,249
(Can she figure out that
these hands belong to Ji-min?)

322
00:17:54,466 --> 00:17:57,371
If he had known beforehand,
he could've applied sesame oil.

323
00:17:59,973 --> 00:18:01,989
I wish she would choose him right away.

324
00:18:04,684 --> 00:18:05,684
Please!

325
00:18:06,042 --> 00:18:09,219
If you've felt his hands enough,
you can move onto the next person.

326
00:18:12,069 --> 00:18:13,069
Don't go!

327
00:18:17,594 --> 00:18:19,396
You're very sweaty.

328
00:18:21,909 --> 00:18:23,377
I bet he's nervous.

329
00:18:23,497 --> 00:18:25,266
He reaches out his hands first.

330
00:18:26,913 --> 00:18:30,565
(Jae-hyung held out his hands first.)

331
00:18:36,353 --> 00:18:39,553
- I have no idea.
- Just go with your feelings.

332
00:18:41,636 --> 00:18:43,081
I really don't know.

333
00:18:44,335 --> 00:18:48,107
(Who will she choose?)

334
00:18:49,937 --> 00:18:53,786
I'll go with the last person.

335
00:18:54,131 --> 00:18:56,178
Things got twisted here!

336
00:18:56,203 --> 00:18:57,894
(A result that no one expected)

337
00:18:59,858 --> 00:19:00,858
Hi.

338
00:19:04,109 --> 00:19:06,045
- We'll go.
- Sure, please go on stage.

339
00:19:07,804 --> 00:19:09,827
She glanced at Ji-min!

340
00:19:09,852 --> 00:19:15,092
I wanted to be with Ji-min, so it's a
bit regrettable I didn't end up with him.

341
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:19,066
(Third up is In-seong.)

342
00:19:19,091 --> 00:19:21,553
I think In-seong lost her drive.

343
00:19:21,758 --> 00:19:22,881
(Careful)

344
00:19:24,211 --> 00:19:26,274
You're not reading his palms, are you?

345
00:19:35,334 --> 00:19:38,770
What's this?
Okay.

346
00:19:43,388 --> 00:19:45,188
You have really warm hands.

347
00:19:50,789 --> 00:19:55,237
(Who will she choose?)

348
00:19:56,434 --> 00:19:58,870
- I'll just go with him.
- "Just."

349
00:20:00,286 --> 00:20:02,191
(What do you mean "just..."?)

350
00:20:03,774 --> 00:20:05,941
Why did you say "just"?

351
00:20:08,153 --> 00:20:11,129
(The third couple is Ji-mnin and In-seong.)

352
00:20:11,281 --> 00:20:14,378
- Why'd you say "just"?
- Because I didn't know who it was.

353
00:20:15,412 --> 00:20:18,081
(Da-Na is the fourth one to go.)

354
00:20:19,004 --> 00:20:20,854
(Won-jae and Jae-hyung are left.)

355
00:20:20,879 --> 00:20:25,388
- They're interested in her, right?
- Yes, they both are.

356
00:20:26,658 --> 00:20:33,231
I didn't get a chance to talk with her a
lot, so I was hoping she'd choose me.

357
00:20:36,079 --> 00:20:37,278
You may start.

358
00:20:39,828 --> 00:20:42,440
(Who will she choose?)

359
00:20:42,465 --> 00:20:43,932
I bet they're nervous.

360
00:20:47,543 --> 00:20:49,146
(Nervous)

361
00:20:57,722 --> 00:21:00,301
I'll go with him.

362
00:21:03,935 --> 00:21:05,808
- What?
- What? Why?

363
00:21:06,628 --> 00:21:07,761
I'll go with him.

364
00:21:10,369 --> 00:21:11,925
You felt really awkward, huh?

365
00:21:17,609 --> 00:21:19,050
(Regrettable)

366
00:21:19,745 --> 00:21:24,701
- Naturally, you two became partners.
- Jae-hyung, you need to go with me.

367
00:21:24,726 --> 00:21:25,726
That's right!

368
00:21:26,630 --> 00:21:27,869
Why didn't you take me?

369
00:21:29,549 --> 00:21:35,489
- Why does this keep...? - Why do
these things keep happening to him?

370
00:21:35,514 --> 00:21:37,539
My heart goes out to him the most.

371
00:21:40,274 --> 00:21:44,790
- New couples.
- Right. New couples keep being born.

372
00:21:47,942 --> 00:21:50,107
We will now practice the couple dance,

373
00:21:50,132 --> 00:21:56,931
but if you create a new kind of ending
pose with your teamwork and creativity,

374
00:21:57,587 --> 00:22:02,531
it will bring you closer to first place.

375
00:22:02,944 --> 00:22:04,822
I can just put you on my shoulder then.

376
00:22:05,688 --> 00:22:08,929
- I can rely on you, right?
- I really suck at dancing.

377
00:22:09,115 --> 00:22:10,781
- Just trust me.
- Okay.

378
00:22:11,036 --> 00:22:12,910
Yeo-min is so cool!

379
00:22:12,935 --> 00:22:18,159
Okay, we'll lightly start off by
practicing holding hands first.

380
00:22:18,505 --> 00:22:19,918
I'm suddenly sweating.

381
00:22:22,541 --> 00:22:25,025
- You're sweating?
- It's 'cause I'm nervous.

382
00:22:26,301 --> 00:22:32,427
Let's start practicing holding
hands to feel the connection.

383
00:22:32,452 --> 00:22:34,933
Look at the mirror.
The women on this side.

384
00:22:34,958 --> 00:22:36,158
Come a bit closer.

385
00:22:36,414 --> 00:22:39,669
In that position, the men
will hold out their hands from

386
00:22:39,694 --> 00:22:43,004
under, and the women will
hold out their hands from above.

387
00:22:43,029 --> 00:22:44,029
Like this?

388
00:22:44,437 --> 00:22:49,747
Great. Touch your palms
together to feel the teamwork.

389
00:22:51,690 --> 00:22:53,651
(The honor couple is doing well.)

390
00:22:54,162 --> 00:22:55,562
- Like this?
- Yeah.

391
00:22:58,395 --> 00:22:59,935
Very nice.

392
00:23:01,515 --> 00:23:03,440
(Stare)

393
00:23:05,354 --> 00:23:08,362
(He carefully holds Ha-neul's hands.)

394
00:23:08,387 --> 00:23:09,387
Oh my goodness.

395
00:23:09,718 --> 00:23:12,784
Let the other person
know you care about them.

396
00:23:13,205 --> 00:23:16,221
I care about you. I care about you.

397
00:23:16,406 --> 00:23:17,406
Is it like this?

398
00:23:18,821 --> 00:23:19,821
Is this right?

399
00:23:19,846 --> 00:23:22,061
(It's the first time their
hands are properly touching.)

400
00:23:24,725 --> 00:23:29,551
(They keep looking at each
other as they face one another.)

401
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:39,698
- As if we're wiping the palms.
- Wiping the palms? Got it.

402
00:23:40,721 --> 00:23:44,163
(They do as the teacher says
but they burst into laughter.)

403
00:23:44,848 --> 00:23:47,459
(So shy!)

404
00:23:50,472 --> 00:23:52,537
(Uncomfortable/Bothered)

405
00:23:54,970 --> 00:23:57,066
Like we're wiping each other's palms. Okay.

406
00:23:57,091 --> 00:23:58,291
Yes, that's right.

407
00:23:58,587 --> 00:24:00,578
Okay. Very nice.

408
00:24:00,603 --> 00:24:07,835
The most important thing here is to not
act embarrassed even though you are.

409
00:24:08,081 --> 00:24:10,248
- Let's try that.
- Goodness.

410
00:24:10,273 --> 00:24:11,838
Here we go.

411
00:24:16,096 --> 00:24:19,660
(They're a bit awkward.)

412
00:24:21,124 --> 00:24:22,624
(Flexible)

413
00:24:23,952 --> 00:24:26,795
(A practice session
filled with heart flutters)

414
00:24:27,639 --> 00:24:28,639
(Freeze)

415
00:24:28,887 --> 00:24:30,332
Put some strength into it!

416
00:24:32,114 --> 00:24:34,764
Wonderful job! Starting now...

417
00:24:34,789 --> 00:24:38,347
(The individual couple
dance practice begins.)

418
00:24:39,581 --> 00:24:40,581
(Smile)

419
00:24:41,177 --> 00:24:42,907
(They never let go.)

420
00:24:46,539 --> 00:24:50,106
- Whoa, we did it.
- It will work out if you lead me.

421
00:24:50,806 --> 00:24:52,631
Okay, then I'll do it.

422
00:24:52,665 --> 00:24:55,127
Even if we mess up, that will help.

423
00:24:55,938 --> 00:24:59,179
(Their practice continues
with Won-jae's lead.)

424
00:25:01,636 --> 00:25:03,295
Just trust me.

425
00:25:04,909 --> 00:25:06,331
(Won-jae is the best!)

426
00:25:06,356 --> 00:25:08,220
My goodness.

427
00:25:10,404 --> 00:25:13,854
Wait a second! I'm leaning
on you too much. Hang on.

428
00:25:13,879 --> 00:25:15,507
- You can lean on me.
- I can? It's okay?

429
00:25:15,532 --> 00:25:17,665
Just come to me. I'll catch you.

430
00:25:17,690 --> 00:25:19,157
Should we do it again?

431
00:25:19,182 --> 00:25:24,076
Won-jae is a bit young,
but he didn't feel that way.

432
00:25:24,382 --> 00:25:26,104
It was... kind of nice.

433
00:25:26,718 --> 00:25:28,687
(Turn, turn)

434
00:25:29,023 --> 00:25:30,608
- We got it.
- Let's do this.

435
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:32,531
Let's do it one more time.

436
00:25:32,556 --> 00:25:35,137
(The more they practice,
the closer they get.)

437
00:25:36,498 --> 00:25:38,601
(Awesome teamwork)

438
00:25:39,152 --> 00:25:41,285
Gosh, it's hot. This is awesome.

439
00:25:42,069 --> 00:25:43,135
It's hot, right?

440
00:25:47,416 --> 00:25:52,956
Before, I said that Da-Na is
very close to my ideal type.

441
00:25:53,986 --> 00:25:57,297
Whenever I made eye contact with her, it
felt like I was looking at my ideal type.

442
00:25:57,562 --> 00:25:59,053
That's how I felt.

443
00:25:59,942 --> 00:26:03,659
So personally, my heart fluttered a lot.

444
00:26:05,038 --> 00:26:08,180
- This is so interesting.
- Won-jae is totally into her.

445
00:26:09,337 --> 00:26:11,622
- We have to make a great
pose at the end. - Right.

446
00:26:11,829 --> 00:26:13,584
Let's try that last pose out.

447
00:26:14,778 --> 00:26:15,904
Here, we'll...

448
00:26:15,929 --> 00:26:19,763
(Their practice is being led by Yeo-min.)

449
00:26:21,579 --> 00:26:22,927
Should I go all the way back?

450
00:26:22,952 --> 00:26:26,580
You can lift your arm and
I'll go back. Look at me.

451
00:26:28,189 --> 00:26:29,760
I think this is good.

452
00:26:29,834 --> 00:26:31,516
Let's fix it up.

453
00:26:32,303 --> 00:26:34,122
She bent backwards. Should we do the same?

454
00:26:34,147 --> 00:26:35,814
- Bend backwards?
- Yeah.

455
00:26:37,636 --> 00:26:38,698
Bend backwards?

456
00:26:39,168 --> 00:26:41,002
- Isn't that too basic?
- Let's try it out.

457
00:26:41,164 --> 00:26:43,116
- You have to bend.
- I do?

458
00:26:43,141 --> 00:26:44,593
- Hey!
- What?

459
00:26:44,618 --> 00:26:46,692
Let's say we do this and you
spin around. Spin.

460
00:26:46,732 --> 00:26:48,940
- Me?
- Yeah, spin around.

461
00:26:48,965 --> 00:26:51,451
Careful. Then lie back.

462
00:26:51,913 --> 00:26:52,913
Like this?

463
00:26:53,968 --> 00:26:56,465
Something feels weird.

464
00:26:56,490 --> 00:26:58,704
- Do it for me.
- Okay.

465
00:26:59,372 --> 00:27:00,470
Like this and...

466
00:27:00,716 --> 00:27:03,771
(Ji-min continuously obsesses
over bending backwards.)

467
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:07,379
I'm so hot.

468
00:27:07,612 --> 00:27:12,224
Jung-woo keeps glancing at In-seong.

469
00:27:12,832 --> 00:27:14,237
(Close)

470
00:27:16,066 --> 00:27:18,933
(For some reason,
his lips keep drying up.)

471
00:27:19,768 --> 00:27:22,236
(They can't stop looking.)

472
00:27:22,415 --> 00:27:24,209
- Straighten up.
- Okay, straighten up.

473
00:27:24,234 --> 00:27:26,569
(They focus on practice
without caring who's looking.)

474
00:27:26,902 --> 00:27:28,283
- The gaze is important.
- I see.

475
00:27:28,308 --> 00:27:29,421
What do I do?

476
00:27:30,087 --> 00:27:32,572
- Kiss you like this?
- That works.

477
00:27:32,997 --> 00:27:33,997
Do it cutely.

478
00:27:34,022 --> 00:27:36,332
(A kiss?)

479
00:27:37,979 --> 00:27:39,756
- You mean it?
- Yeah, I don't really care.

480
00:27:39,781 --> 00:27:42,941
(Even with his earpods,
he can hear the word "kiss.")

481
00:27:43,836 --> 00:27:45,924
(In-seong's proactive actions)

482
00:27:45,949 --> 00:27:47,076
Then I can kiss you.

483
00:27:47,101 --> 00:27:49,013
- Oh, yes! That's right!
- Yeah!

484
00:27:55,346 --> 00:27:58,146
- They were shocked.
- See? He's sighing.

485
00:27:58,171 --> 00:28:00,119
I can't tell how Jung-woo feels either.

486
00:28:01,162 --> 00:28:03,737
(They're not even
thinking of getting up.)

487
00:28:03,762 --> 00:28:08,207
Let's watch the video first.
We'll learn with our eyes first.

488
00:28:10,187 --> 00:28:11,957
(Glance)

489
00:28:12,098 --> 00:28:13,964
(The others are
practicing away.)

490
00:28:13,989 --> 00:28:17,048
(And Ji-min is the most enthusiastic one.)

491
00:28:17,444 --> 00:28:20,946
(They seemed to have lost ambition.)

492
00:28:21,073 --> 00:28:23,247
- Are we really memorizing
it with our eyes? - Huh?

493
00:28:23,272 --> 00:28:24,747
Are we memorizing it with our eyes?

494
00:28:24,772 --> 00:28:29,361
If we watch it, at least we
won't be clueless when we do it.

495
00:28:30,090 --> 00:28:32,232
I don't know what to do for the ending.

496
00:28:32,559 --> 00:28:36,131
- You can lie down.
- Oh, lean back?

497
00:28:36,888 --> 00:28:39,674
- Can you hold me?
- Yeah, of course.

498
00:28:40,625 --> 00:28:44,926
- Like this...
- Don't I spin around like this?

499
00:28:45,453 --> 00:28:49,756
Right. Like this. But just fully lean back.

500
00:28:51,740 --> 00:28:54,136
Don't worry about that.
If you worry about it...

501
00:28:54,751 --> 00:28:58,028
Like this...
