751
00:42:51,595 --> 00:42:52,809
Just a little in the past.

752
00:42:53,763 --> 00:42:55,445
That was enjoyable. Good job.

753
00:42:59,270 --> 00:43:01,659
We saw the dances of all five couples.

754
00:43:01,684 --> 00:43:05,382
Su-won and Ha-neul.
Have you ever danced before, Su-won?

755
00:43:05,767 --> 00:43:07,758
- It's my first time.
- It is?

756
00:43:07,857 --> 00:43:10,216
- Yes.
- You've never leaned before? Wow.

757
00:43:10,241 --> 00:43:11,827
- You have talent.
- Are you lying?

758
00:43:11,852 --> 00:43:12,852
I mean it.

759
00:43:13,355 --> 00:43:18,760
Su-won was really proactive,
and that was very nice to see.

760
00:43:19,474 --> 00:43:21,934
Her comments can really be accurate.

761
00:43:21,959 --> 00:43:24,325
You can see feelings through dances.

762
00:43:24,996 --> 00:43:27,796
- She said Su-won was proactive.
- Right.

763
00:43:27,821 --> 00:43:29,958
- She was able to see that.
- That's fascinating.

764
00:43:30,382 --> 00:43:32,787
Ji-min and In-seong.

765
00:43:33,727 --> 00:43:36,855
In-seong was determined to do her best,

766
00:43:36,880 --> 00:43:41,396
and Ji-min was proactive and confident.

767
00:43:41,584 --> 00:43:43,155
So you two seemed like an ideal couple.

768
00:43:44,451 --> 00:43:45,991
They looked like a couple.

769
00:43:46,016 --> 00:43:48,413
Jae-hyung and Yeo-min.

770
00:43:48,438 --> 00:43:51,981
When you try your best
instead of trying to look nice,

771
00:43:52,006 --> 00:43:56,716
it looks so much more beautiful
because you can see that sincerity.

772
00:43:57,036 --> 00:44:02,766
The both of you had bullets in your eyes,
and you were shooting them at each other.

773
00:44:03,010 --> 00:44:04,303
Bang, bang, bang!

774
00:44:04,751 --> 00:44:08,195
I saw that, and just by that, I
want to give you a hundred points.

775
00:44:08,540 --> 00:44:10,930
- You did a splendid job.
- They got the best compliment.

776
00:44:10,955 --> 00:44:12,680
They're pretty much the winners.

777
00:44:12,705 --> 00:44:19,175
The winners of this challenge have
the chance to enter the Room of Secrets

778
00:44:20,602 --> 00:44:23,537
(The Room of Secrets)

779
00:44:23,804 --> 00:44:26,541
(The winners of the
challenge can check a

780
00:44:26,566 --> 00:44:29,497
participant's secret in
the Room of Secrets.)

781
00:44:29,929 --> 00:44:34,104
I will now announce the winners.

782
00:44:34,863 --> 00:44:36,640
Is it Jae-hyung and Yeo-min?

783
00:44:38,756 --> 00:44:41,017
- Won-jae did a terrific job, too.
- Right.

784
00:44:41,160 --> 00:44:43,328
- Ji-min and In-seong kissed, too.
- Yeah.

785
00:44:43,353 --> 00:44:46,522
The winners are Jae-hyung and Yeo-min.

786
00:44:48,358 --> 00:44:50,827
Thank you!
Thank you!

787
00:44:52,745 --> 00:44:54,897
- Great job.
- You did a wonderful job.

788
00:44:56,109 --> 00:44:58,403
(She's definitely a dancer!)

789
00:44:58,428 --> 00:45:03,332
- Yeo-min is the Queen of Challenges!
- She keeps winning!

790
00:45:04,703 --> 00:45:07,172
(The dance challenge comes to an end...)

791
00:45:07,612 --> 00:45:10,016
(and they head towards the Love Mansion.)

792
00:45:10,400 --> 00:45:12,495
- You worked really hard today.
- Yeah.

793
00:45:12,520 --> 00:45:14,410
- Great work.
- You really went through a lot.

794
00:45:14,435 --> 00:45:16,206
- No.
- They're going back together.

795
00:45:16,343 --> 00:45:19,367
I kept forgetting the
moves. I felt so bad.

796
00:45:19,742 --> 00:45:22,005
What did you forget?
You didn't forget anything.

797
00:45:22,380 --> 00:45:23,380
Thanks.

798
00:45:23,689 --> 00:45:29,536
You kind of slipped, so I wondered if you
were being considerate in case I felt bad.

799
00:45:30,572 --> 00:45:32,492
- That's what I thought.
- That was my mistake.

800
00:45:32,517 --> 00:45:33,724
- Really?
- Yeah.

801
00:45:33,749 --> 00:45:37,044
I think I saw a new side of you today.

802
00:45:37,713 --> 00:45:38,713
That's good.

803
00:45:39,651 --> 00:45:40,939
I'm actually nosier.

804
00:45:42,250 --> 00:45:44,179
But this is really nice.

805
00:45:44,779 --> 00:45:46,966
- He said it's nice.
- He confessed to her.

806
00:45:50,317 --> 00:45:52,959
- Let's open the window.
- There are so many stars tonight.

807
00:45:52,984 --> 00:45:54,054
- Really?
- Yeah.

808
00:45:54,079 --> 00:45:56,097
This needs to be
turned off to see better.

809
00:45:56,122 --> 00:45:58,949
- Let's see them at home.
- Take a look. How is it?

810
00:46:00,382 --> 00:46:03,694
- Can you see them?
- Yeah, there are a ton of stars.

811
00:46:04,410 --> 00:46:07,148
What's this? Why is it so romantic?

812
00:46:07,723 --> 00:46:10,262
- Do you like looking at stars?
- I love it.

813
00:46:10,813 --> 00:46:12,916
- I really love looking at stars.
- For real?

814
00:46:12,941 --> 00:46:15,427
I just like staring into space.

815
00:46:15,452 --> 00:46:19,135
- Just blanking out.
- I just like not doing anything.

816
00:46:19,160 --> 00:46:21,402
It's nice that we get to
talk about things like this.

817
00:46:22,064 --> 00:46:24,658
They're a good match.
They have similar sensibilities.

818
00:46:25,264 --> 00:46:27,184
(Meanwhile)

819
00:46:27,209 --> 00:46:33,597
I'm actually really
grateful to Ji-min tonight.

820
00:46:34,497 --> 00:46:39,412
- Why? - In the middle, I kind
of had a mental breakdown.

821
00:46:39,437 --> 00:46:42,081
- I know.
- So I left the room for a bit.

822
00:46:42,106 --> 00:46:45,601
When I came back, he didn't ask me
anything. He didn't ask me if I was okay.

823
00:46:45,626 --> 00:46:47,762
He just cheered me up right away.

824
00:46:48,829 --> 00:46:51,229
What's with you?
What's up with you?

825
00:46:51,956 --> 00:46:54,355
- You're so cool.
- I want to hide.

826
00:46:54,380 --> 00:46:56,676
Why? That was cool. Why
would you be embarrassed?

827
00:46:58,483 --> 00:47:00,467
Ji-min is the definition of sweet.

828
00:47:01,538 --> 00:47:03,398
Don't say that in front of Su-won!

829
00:47:04,632 --> 00:47:07,032
What about you?
What are you doing?

830
00:47:08,885 --> 00:47:12,557
(All Su-won does is
give a mysterious smile.)

831
00:47:13,087 --> 00:47:19,692
I already went on two dates with you
already, so I didn't feel any pressure.

832
00:47:19,717 --> 00:47:22,767
But you seemed embarrassed.

833
00:47:23,254 --> 00:47:25,406
I think I was more embarrassed
because I was with you.

834
00:47:26,028 --> 00:47:29,417
I thought the opposite because
we've talked a few times.

835
00:47:29,873 --> 00:47:32,064
- But we weren't comfortable.
- I did feel comfortable.

836
00:47:32,089 --> 00:47:36,193
- You kept thinking in a strange way.
- I didn't.

837
00:47:38,073 --> 00:47:39,732
You just said you weren't comfortable.

838
00:47:39,757 --> 00:47:44,346
There's nothing strange, but being
partners with you makes me a bit more...

839
00:47:44,371 --> 00:47:45,638
What? What's wrong?

840
00:47:45,756 --> 00:47:46,756
Of all people...

841
00:47:48,493 --> 00:47:49,760
how did we end up together?

842
00:47:49,958 --> 00:47:51,045
"Of all people."

843
00:47:52,191 --> 00:47:54,032
I think she said the wrong thing.

844
00:47:54,057 --> 00:47:56,057
She probably thought
"oh, no" after she said that.

845
00:47:56,187 --> 00:47:57,187
Of all people...

846
00:47:58,973 --> 00:48:00,417
how did we end up together?

847
00:48:01,097 --> 00:48:03,364
But still, it was your ideal hand.

848
00:48:03,576 --> 00:48:05,450
It could just be my hand she likes.

849
00:48:05,475 --> 00:48:08,355
- What does that have to do with
ideal type? - Yeah, you never know.

850
00:48:10,049 --> 00:48:13,161
- There's something odd going on.
- The atmosphere is really weird.

851
00:48:17,107 --> 00:48:21,463
I went on all three dates
with Ha-neul, you know.

852
00:48:21,944 --> 00:48:28,127
But since I'm only paying attention to her,

853
00:48:28,669 --> 00:48:32,830
I could feel that the other
four girls are excluding me.

854
00:48:32,855 --> 00:48:33,855
Right.

855
00:48:35,443 --> 00:48:37,689
But on the other hand,
you're not like that.

856
00:48:38,197 --> 00:48:43,056
You're close to all the guys.

857
00:48:43,873 --> 00:48:50,031
Yeah, but I'm also worried if
something else will develop from that.

858
00:48:51,205 --> 00:48:53,055
Did something happen?

859
00:48:54,397 --> 00:48:56,664
There's emotional conflict between them.

860
00:48:57,677 --> 00:48:59,862
(She soothes her anxious throat.)

861
00:49:01,382 --> 00:49:03,240
Anyhow, it's an uncomfortable conversation.

862
00:49:06,022 --> 00:49:08,999
(Love Mansion)

863
00:49:09,963 --> 00:49:11,828
- Are we the first ones here?
- I think so.

864
00:49:12,522 --> 00:49:14,736
(Ji-min and Su-won came back first.)

865
00:49:15,136 --> 00:49:17,112
I don't think I'm making any progress here.

866
00:49:17,572 --> 00:49:21,209
I realized that after seeing things like
your direction and expressions of interest.

867
00:49:21,515 --> 00:49:22,515
You don't know that.

868
00:49:22,737 --> 00:49:26,732
Do you think things will always be
the same for me? You don't know that.

869
00:49:28,356 --> 00:49:32,556
I think it's true that everyone has
experienced major emotional changes today.

870
00:49:33,075 --> 00:49:34,675
Why do you look so down?

871
00:49:35,241 --> 00:49:37,283
I'm not down. I just have a lot on my mind.

872
00:49:37,588 --> 00:49:39,960
- Oh, right.
- What do I do about my Love Coin?

873
00:49:40,361 --> 00:49:43,067
You were partners with Su-won,
but you're not going to choose him?

874
00:49:45,032 --> 00:49:46,232
That's ridiculous.

875
00:49:46,494 --> 00:49:50,248
I think everyone thinks
they're a definite couple.

876
00:49:50,602 --> 00:49:52,354
It's not that you don't
know who to choose.

877
00:49:52,465 --> 00:49:55,571
You just don't know if
you should choose him.

878
00:49:55,596 --> 00:49:57,796
Right. That's always the problem.

879
00:49:59,587 --> 00:50:01,214
The two of us already voted.

880
00:50:01,762 --> 00:50:03,962
What will you three do?

881
00:50:04,498 --> 00:50:06,544
Honestly, my heart changed every day.

882
00:50:06,569 --> 00:50:08,444
- Really?
- He's so honest.

883
00:50:08,469 --> 00:50:09,817
One change per day.

884
00:50:11,274 --> 00:50:12,474
I changed my mind.

885
00:50:12,869 --> 00:50:16,561
You, too? I thought
you would never do that.

886
00:50:16,629 --> 00:50:17,946
Why not?

887
00:50:18,049 --> 00:50:19,525
I mean, given the circumstances...

888
00:50:21,357 --> 00:50:22,623
But I have a reason.

889
00:50:23,189 --> 00:50:24,324
A reason?

890
00:50:25,179 --> 00:50:26,179
Really?

891
00:50:26,998 --> 00:50:29,264
- So his heart changed?
- I know.

892
00:50:29,408 --> 00:50:31,048
(Curious)

893
00:50:31,757 --> 00:50:32,890
I can't tell you.

894
00:50:33,392 --> 00:50:35,258
But that's how I felt today.

895
00:50:37,619 --> 00:50:39,993
Everyone is in a
complicated situation today.

896
00:50:42,513 --> 00:50:45,505
(The screen suddenly turns on.)

897
00:50:45,753 --> 00:50:47,086
The Room of Secrets?

898
00:50:49,572 --> 00:50:53,329
(Please go check your lockers.)

899
00:50:53,354 --> 00:50:55,438
What?

900
00:50:55,859 --> 00:50:56,926
There's tension.

901
00:50:57,537 --> 00:51:00,330
I don't want to check it.
Why don't I want to check it today?

902
00:51:01,620 --> 00:51:05,219
Wow, it'd be really fun if they played a
Truth Game after checking their lockers.

903
00:51:05,958 --> 00:51:08,125
Right. It'll turn into a battlefield.

904
00:51:08,676 --> 00:51:11,637
(Meanwhile, the screen
turned on in the men's lodging.)

905
00:51:11,677 --> 00:51:14,934
What's that? Hey! It said we
have to go check our lockers.

906
00:51:15,063 --> 00:51:17,730
- The lockers? - Oh, I bet it appeared
in the dining room, too.

907
00:51:18,455 --> 00:51:19,844
Come to the dining room.

908
00:51:22,420 --> 00:51:24,278
- Go on.
- I should go first.

909
00:51:25,391 --> 00:51:26,924
Alright, I'll go first.

910
00:51:28,093 --> 00:51:29,720
Is she going now?

911
00:51:29,745 --> 00:51:32,166
(Yeo-min is heading to the
Room of Expressing Interests.)

912
00:51:32,730 --> 00:51:34,269
Yeo-min.

913
00:51:39,287 --> 00:51:42,510
- I think they're trying to not
show us their expressions. - Really?

914
00:51:42,743 --> 00:51:45,005
It's actually a problematic day.

915
00:51:48,545 --> 00:51:51,662
(Ha-neul walks with heavy steps.)

916
00:51:53,691 --> 00:51:55,429
Oh, they're showing us Ha-neul.

917
00:51:57,761 --> 00:52:03,729
Su-won is the one who I'm
the most attracted to right now.

918
00:52:04,115 --> 00:52:06,123
So I was hoping his coin was in my locker.

919
00:52:07,285 --> 00:52:08,881
She still likes him.

920
00:52:10,099 --> 00:52:12,281
- Ha-neul had two coins, right?
- Yeah.

921
00:52:14,373 --> 00:52:17,030
(Lee Ha-neul: 0 Votes)

922
00:52:17,150 --> 00:52:18,446
(What happened?)

923
00:52:18,471 --> 00:52:20,400
Su-won's feelings must have changed.

924
00:52:21,253 --> 00:52:22,411
I can't believe it!

925
00:52:22,436 --> 00:52:24,556
It's shocking that his coin is gone.

926
00:52:24,940 --> 00:52:27,281
Ha-neul suddenly became
someone with zero votes.

927
00:52:28,498 --> 00:52:30,244
- You're already done?
- Yeah.

928
00:52:35,014 --> 00:52:38,188
Then Ha-neul could completely
have a change of heart.

929
00:52:38,427 --> 00:52:39,619
Through this?

930
00:52:41,123 --> 00:52:44,408
(Su-won arrived in the dining room.)

931
00:52:45,969 --> 00:52:48,643
That popped up in the room, too.
I guess it showed up here, too.

932
00:52:50,346 --> 00:52:51,600
She's not looking at him.

933
00:52:51,952 --> 00:52:56,185
- Did you see the screen?
- Yeah, I saw the one in the room.

934
00:52:58,237 --> 00:53:00,104
- Wow.
- What will they do?

935
00:53:00,802 --> 00:53:03,517
(Su-won has no idea that the
women already checked their lockers.)

936
00:53:03,542 --> 00:53:06,282
The guys should go, too.

937
00:53:06,307 --> 00:53:08,568
- Yeah, we should.
- "Too."

938
00:53:14,338 --> 00:53:17,056
- Oh no.
- Now he knows.

939
00:53:17,666 --> 00:53:18,666
Go on.

940
00:53:20,967 --> 00:53:22,681
The atmosphere is suddenly...

941
00:53:23,173 --> 00:53:24,573
It got a lot awkward.

942
00:53:26,808 --> 00:53:32,779
If there's a Love Coin in
Su-won's locker, then he's doomed.

943
00:53:32,804 --> 00:53:34,787
He'll feel so bad.

944
00:53:38,102 --> 00:53:41,342
(It's the moment when the door
that he has always opened...)

945
00:53:41,367 --> 00:53:42,834
(feels heavier today.)

946
00:53:42,859 --> 00:53:45,910
- I feel like he has at least one.
- Yeah, I think there is one.

947
00:53:47,017 --> 00:53:48,837
- It's there, right?
- Is it there or not?

948
00:53:48,862 --> 00:53:51,496
(Jung Su-won: 1 Vote)

949
00:53:52,302 --> 00:53:55,431
- Why did you do that?
- My goodness.

950
00:53:56,982 --> 00:54:01,013
I think it's from Ha-neul.

951
00:54:04,561 --> 00:54:06,045
He's not going to the dining room.

952
00:54:08,603 --> 00:54:10,476
- I need to talk to you.
- What?

953
00:54:10,501 --> 00:54:12,741
- I need to talk to you.
- What? About what?

954
00:54:13,234 --> 00:54:15,172
(What's going on?)

955
00:54:17,003 --> 00:54:19,867
There's so much on her mind, so
she looked for someone she can vent to.

956
00:54:22,016 --> 00:54:23,714
You know, I...

957
00:54:26,671 --> 00:54:28,205
I don't have any coins.

958
00:54:28,949 --> 00:54:30,949
- Really?
- Yes, I have none.

959
00:54:31,843 --> 00:54:33,549
But I kept pondering about this, too.

960
00:54:33,574 --> 00:54:35,567
And I just left mine in his locker.

961
00:54:36,770 --> 00:54:40,913
I feel like he made me into a fool,
so I'm not very happy right now.

962
00:54:40,938 --> 00:54:41,938
I know.

963
00:54:43,785 --> 00:54:46,634
He probably does feel
bad because he took my

964
00:54:46,659 --> 00:54:49,444
coin away but saw I
left mine in his locker.

965
00:54:50,339 --> 00:54:53,442
But he didn't give me any hints about this.

966
00:54:55,489 --> 00:54:58,385
I just feel like a fool...

967
00:54:59,603 --> 00:55:02,897
If he was going to do this, why did he
say all those things in front of everyone?

968
00:55:02,922 --> 00:55:04,167
I know.

969
00:55:07,132 --> 00:55:08,815
That's why she looked so gloomy.

970
00:55:08,840 --> 00:55:11,659
(Su-won is in the dining room.)

971
00:55:12,934 --> 00:55:15,974
- What? Why are you guys drinking?
- 'Cause we want to.

972
00:55:15,999 --> 00:55:17,421
Ha-neul, let's have a drink.

973
00:55:20,179 --> 00:55:21,856
I'm cold. It's freezing.

974
00:55:21,881 --> 00:55:23,768
This is nice. Have
some steamed eggs.

975
00:55:24,383 --> 00:55:26,899
- You said your cold.
- Oh, so I can be warm?

976
00:55:27,178 --> 00:55:28,178
Thanks.

977
00:55:29,826 --> 00:55:31,444
(He wordlessly raises
the temperature.)

978
00:55:31,469 --> 00:55:33,336
All his attention is on her.

979
00:55:33,511 --> 00:55:35,028
You said you're hungry. Eat up.

980
00:55:35,514 --> 00:55:36,609
I'm not hungry.

981
00:55:36,634 --> 00:55:38,093
- Really? You're not?
- Yeah.

982
00:55:38,572 --> 00:55:40,866
- You didn't eat though.
- Have the steamed eggs.

983
00:55:42,784 --> 00:55:45,554
- Aren't you going to drink soju?
- How can I drink that?

984
00:55:46,406 --> 00:55:47,945
- Do you want soju?
- Yeah.

985
00:55:47,970 --> 00:55:51,099
I want to drink with you.
I want to have soju with you.

986
00:55:52,049 --> 00:55:53,348
He's suddenly going in.

987
00:55:55,327 --> 00:55:57,653
- What's wrong with you?
- Why are you laughing?

988
00:55:58,665 --> 00:56:01,688
Is he expressing his feelings because
he thinks this is the right moment?

989
00:56:03,399 --> 00:56:05,344
Ji-min, wanna go out?

990
00:56:05,856 --> 00:56:07,260
Oh, what was that?

991
00:56:07,792 --> 00:56:08,792
"Wanna go out?"

992
00:56:08,817 --> 00:56:10,613
Ji-min, wanna go out?

993
00:56:11,352 --> 00:56:13,035
No. There's nothing I can tell you.

994
00:56:13,060 --> 00:56:14,927
Then why are you doing this?

995
00:56:15,596 --> 00:56:18,389
I'm just... I'm sorry.

996
00:56:19,409 --> 00:56:23,401
Ji-min is apologizing because
he took his coin from her locker, too.

997
00:56:23,499 --> 00:56:25,985
- That's true.
- I think that's what he's doing.

998
00:56:26,010 --> 00:56:27,010
What's wrong?

999
00:56:28,107 --> 00:56:29,107
Me?

1000
00:56:30,561 --> 00:56:32,125
I don't know.

1001
00:56:33,965 --> 00:56:35,441
- Wanna go out?
- Sure.

1002
00:56:37,554 --> 00:56:39,101
Oh no, Su-won.

1003
00:56:40,772 --> 00:56:42,900
I have no idea how Su-won feels.

1004
00:56:42,925 --> 00:56:44,525
He's clearly interested.

1005
00:56:46,512 --> 00:56:48,899
(Ha-neul and Ji-min came outside.)

1006
00:56:50,844 --> 00:56:54,125
(They stayed silent for a long time.)

1007
00:56:56,068 --> 00:56:57,917
- I think you know.
- About what?

1008
00:56:58,354 --> 00:56:59,354
That I'm upset.

1009
00:57:01,096 --> 00:57:02,096
I assumed.

1010
00:57:03,552 --> 00:57:06,154
- Honestly, I thought a lot today.
- About what?

1011
00:57:06,179 --> 00:57:07,410
About the votes.

1012
00:57:07,435 --> 00:57:10,191
- So I do understand Su-won's decision.
- Okay.

1013
00:57:11,433 --> 00:57:12,972
I get it, but...

1014
00:57:16,008 --> 00:57:19,089
(Unlike her mind, her heart
can't really understand him.)

1015
00:57:19,114 --> 00:57:22,513
It would've been nice if
he had told me beforehand.

1016
00:57:23,029 --> 00:57:24,029
Told you what?

1017
00:57:24,606 --> 00:57:27,139
His feelings and how they're changing.

1018
00:57:27,974 --> 00:57:32,474
Do I need to call Su-won out
and listen to what he has to say?

1019
00:57:33,668 --> 00:57:37,433
I don't think Ji-min came out
here to talk to her about this.

1020
00:57:38,239 --> 00:57:42,302
You don't usually ask for dating
advice from your romantic interest, right?

1021
00:57:42,327 --> 00:57:44,274
Right. Is it because they're really close?

1022
00:57:45,215 --> 00:57:49,707
Do I need to call Su-won out
and listen to what he has to say?

1023
00:57:50,467 --> 00:57:52,665
- I'm so...
- You can do that on one condition.

1024
00:57:53,451 --> 00:57:55,086
If you have feelings for him.

1025
00:57:57,610 --> 00:58:01,069
You know that Su-won is interested in you.

1026
00:58:01,240 --> 00:58:03,541
Yeah. I'm really scared right now.

1027
00:58:03,845 --> 00:58:06,663
I'm just so scared to
do anything with anyone.

1028
00:58:07,103 --> 00:58:08,635
Each of my actions...

1029
00:58:10,659 --> 00:58:12,592
could end up hurting someone.

1030
00:58:12,617 --> 00:58:14,506
So to make that happen less...

1031
00:58:14,800 --> 00:58:17,133
This is tough. I'm about to cry.

1032
00:58:19,609 --> 00:58:22,228
I'm similar to you. I
don't want to hurt them.

1033
00:58:23,945 --> 00:58:26,828
I was worried that I'd get hurt,
and I really got hurt, Ji-min.

1034
00:58:27,386 --> 00:58:32,116
I hope you can open your
heart before you end up like me.

1035
00:58:37,952 --> 00:58:39,547
I really thought a lot about it.

1036
00:58:41,036 --> 00:58:44,782
Before I went to express
how I felt, I truly pondered a lot.

1037
00:58:45,327 --> 00:58:49,723
So on one hand, I do
understand his decision.

1038
00:58:50,109 --> 00:58:51,354
He could've had the same...

1039
00:58:52,830 --> 00:58:54,158
thought as me...

1040
00:58:56,228 --> 00:58:59,179
(She tried to hold back her
tears, but they eventually burst.)

1041
00:59:02,455 --> 00:59:05,907
She understands with
her mind but not her heart.

1042
00:59:05,932 --> 00:59:08,054
- To accept it...
- Yes, it's not easy.

1043
00:59:09,215 --> 00:59:11,349
I'm sorry. It's because I drank.

1044
00:59:17,884 --> 00:59:20,035
It's true that I thought
he was a Money Catcher.

1045
00:59:21,492 --> 00:59:23,690
"Why would he do this to me?"

1046
00:59:25,059 --> 00:59:27,574
For me, it's one person.

1047
00:59:29,048 --> 00:59:31,086
Am I the one person that
you mentioned last night?

1048
00:59:31,111 --> 00:59:34,412
Yes, just one person for me. You.

1049
00:59:35,920 --> 00:59:38,141
"How could he be sure from the first day?"

1050
00:59:41,290 --> 00:59:43,353
You should go on
dates with the other girls.

1051
00:59:44,274 --> 00:59:46,412
If you tell me to, I will. I
should do what you say.

1052
00:59:47,377 --> 00:59:48,836
If you tell me not to, I won't.

1053
00:59:50,085 --> 00:59:51,244
I was just scared.

1054
00:59:53,852 --> 00:59:55,748
When he was so straightforward with me,

1055
00:59:56,875 --> 00:59:59,705
the first thing I thought was
that he was going to abandon me.

1056
01:00:00,523 --> 01:00:01,778
So I...

1057
01:00:06,619 --> 01:00:10,753
I had no idea I'd feel
this kind of emotion here.

1058
01:00:11,968 --> 01:00:15,005
"What if I really like him but he changes?"

1059
01:00:16,407 --> 01:00:18,474
"Or what if this is all a lie?"

1060
01:00:19,322 --> 01:00:21,935
To be honest, because
of all those thoughts,

1061
01:00:21,968 --> 01:00:24,157
I couldn't be honest in front of Su-won.

1062
01:00:25,782 --> 01:00:29,400
Ho-jun was right. They
have different speeds.

1063
01:00:29,967 --> 01:00:32,117
(Her tears won't stop
due to sorrow and regret.)

1064
01:00:32,142 --> 01:00:34,276
She was just protecting herself.

1065
01:00:38,859 --> 01:00:39,859
I don't know.

1066
01:00:41,001 --> 01:00:42,464
Will his heart change?

1067
01:00:43,527 --> 01:00:45,127
I don't think it will.

1068
01:00:46,668 --> 01:00:48,602
Ha-neul's heart opened too late.

1069
01:00:49,800 --> 01:00:54,904
I think I'll have to sort out
my feelings on my own now.

1070
01:00:55,430 --> 01:00:57,565
Su-won changed his mind.

1071
01:00:57,590 --> 01:01:00,227
- He took it out.
- Oh no.

1072
01:01:00,252 --> 01:01:01,873
(That's unfortunate.)

1073
01:01:01,898 --> 01:01:04,114
(We've all experienced
the awry speed of hearts.)

1074
01:01:04,139 --> 01:01:05,971
It's bitter.

1075
01:01:06,881 --> 01:01:10,396
Their timing didn't match
since they're at different speeds.

1076
01:01:11,114 --> 01:01:12,714
It's really unfortunate. Really.

1077
01:01:12,739 --> 01:01:16,610
Honestly, doesn't falling in love
at first sight happen to anyone?

1078
01:01:16,811 --> 01:01:19,965
But she was wondering
why he was doing all

1079
01:01:19,990 --> 01:01:23,510
those things to her and
she was doubtful of him.

1080
01:01:23,883 --> 01:01:25,748
I do understand her.

1081
01:01:25,773 --> 01:01:28,862
After all this, you don't think
she's a Money Catcher, do you?

1082
01:01:28,887 --> 01:01:29,893
(Dizzy)

1083
01:01:29,918 --> 01:01:31,318
(She's probably not.)

1084
01:01:31,343 --> 01:01:33,493
But where did everyone go?

1085
01:01:33,687 --> 01:01:36,107
Ha-neul and Ji-min went to talk outside.

1086
01:01:36,132 --> 01:01:38,848
- Right.
- Does she have a lot to say?

1087
01:01:39,509 --> 01:01:41,509
- Dunno. They went to talk.
- Really?

1088
01:01:41,767 --> 01:01:46,442
It's a pity that all these
misunderstandings are piling up.

1089
01:01:47,195 --> 01:01:48,655
But does everyone...

1090
01:01:49,884 --> 01:01:53,635
have complex thoughts?
Is there a lot you want to say?

1091
01:01:53,660 --> 01:01:55,478
- Of course.
- It's complicated.

1092
01:01:55,503 --> 01:01:58,243
We all checked our lockers, too.

1093
01:01:58,334 --> 01:02:00,976
- So I'm sure it's complicated.
- Right. We checked that today.

1094
01:02:01,759 --> 01:02:02,798
That's possible.

1095
01:02:03,386 --> 01:02:04,877
Su-won is disturbed.

1096
01:02:05,174 --> 01:02:08,342
Our thoughts are different from the
first day we expressed our interests.

1097
01:02:10,228 --> 01:02:14,578
I had no idea that everyone
had a lot on their minds.

1098
01:02:15,980 --> 01:02:18,025
(Complicated)

1099
01:02:18,831 --> 01:02:21,418
- Are you alright?
- I'm barely hanging in there.

1100
01:02:22,280 --> 01:02:24,168
I'm calming down.
I'm calming down.

1101
01:02:26,825 --> 01:02:30,937
Just FYI, let me know if you're sick.
I really brought all kinds of medicine.

1102
01:02:30,962 --> 01:02:33,383
- I'm not sick.
- I have herbal tonic, too.

1103
01:02:34,474 --> 01:02:35,874
I brought everything.

1104
01:02:38,694 --> 01:02:41,686
What if your heart aches?
What kind of medicine should I take?

1105
01:02:42,158 --> 01:02:43,213
What should I do?

1106
01:02:43,238 --> 01:02:45,999
First, watch a sad movie
and bawl your eyes out.

1107
01:02:46,024 --> 01:02:48,455
- I have to cry?
- Sob your heart out.

1108
01:02:49,380 --> 01:02:51,110
The medicine he needs is Ha-neul.

1109
01:02:51,771 --> 01:02:54,500
(Just then, Ha-neul and Ji-min
return after they finish talking.)

1110
01:02:54,525 --> 01:02:56,122
- You're back.
- Hi.

1111
01:02:56,484 --> 01:02:57,617
Where's the soju?

1112
01:02:58,055 --> 01:03:01,443
- Oh no.
- Why did Ha-neul's face turn so red?

1113
01:03:04,484 --> 01:03:05,484
It's not red.

1114
01:03:06,230 --> 01:03:07,230
It's not bad.

1115
01:03:07,533 --> 01:03:09,113
It IS red.

1116
01:03:09,966 --> 01:03:11,032
Oh, this is bad.

1117
01:03:12,508 --> 01:03:14,126
Does he not know she cried?

1118
01:03:14,151 --> 01:03:15,771
I hope they can talk.

1119
01:03:15,804 --> 01:03:17,685
You two should go cool your faces down.

1120
01:03:19,809 --> 01:03:22,078
- He's totally helping them.
- Yeah.

1121
01:03:23,813 --> 01:03:26,241
We can just talk here.
We don't need to go out.

1122
01:03:28,383 --> 01:03:31,819
- Su-won tends to say the opposite
of how he feels. - I know!

1123
01:03:32,545 --> 01:03:35,394
- That fool.
- He should've just gone along with it.

1124
01:03:39,203 --> 01:03:40,647
Ha-neul, drink with me.

1125
01:03:40,672 --> 01:03:43,735
(Won-jae tries to loosen
the tense atmosphere.)

1126
01:03:44,714 --> 01:03:45,984
Cheers!

1127
01:03:48,816 --> 01:03:51,117
- Should we play that game from yesterday?
- What game?

1128
01:03:51,142 --> 01:03:52,674
There's a lie detector back there.

1129
01:03:53,582 --> 01:03:55,423
Let's ask heated questions.

1130
01:03:55,448 --> 01:03:57,981
Or should we just have an honest talk?

1131
01:03:58,206 --> 01:04:00,951
- Without that?
- Without it? Sure.

1132
01:04:01,686 --> 01:04:03,074
Go ahead, Jung-woo.

1133
01:04:04,730 --> 01:04:06,324
Wow, this is the most important moment.

1134
01:04:06,349 --> 01:04:08,237
This is his first time
playing this game.

1135
01:04:08,955 --> 01:04:10,129
It's going to be fun.

1136
01:04:10,154 --> 01:04:12,464
He'll definitely ask
someone he's interested in.

1137
01:04:15,717 --> 01:04:18,653
I want to ask her.

1138
01:04:19,061 --> 01:04:20,227
Me? What is it?

1139
01:04:20,505 --> 01:04:22,976
- He wants to ask In-seong?
- What about Da-Na?

1140
01:04:24,902 --> 01:04:27,949
Are you interested in
two or more people here?

1141
01:04:28,484 --> 01:04:29,563
- Interested?
- Yes.

1142
01:04:29,588 --> 01:04:31,855
- As of right now.
- Two or more?

1143
01:04:32,040 --> 01:04:33,861
No.

1144
01:04:34,917 --> 01:04:36,131
- It's just one person.
- One?

1145
01:04:36,156 --> 01:04:37,156
Yes.

1146
01:04:37,359 --> 01:04:39,279
- Whoa, so cool.
- She's firm.

1147
01:04:39,304 --> 01:04:40,622
Yes, she didn't hesitate.

1148
01:04:41,245 --> 01:04:43,879
- It's your turn to ask.
- Oh, okay.

1149
01:04:45,621 --> 01:04:46,754
Who should I ask?

1150
01:04:48,386 --> 01:04:51,236
- Should I ask instead of you?
- Whoa! No way! Ji-min!

1151
01:04:51,261 --> 01:04:53,293
- Whoa, seriously?
- No, but the same question!

1152
01:04:53,318 --> 01:04:55,231
Are you interested in one or two people?

1153
01:04:56,845 --> 01:04:59,146
- No one asked him.
- Oh, me?

1154
01:05:00,532 --> 01:05:01,532
(Curious)

1155
01:05:02,788 --> 01:05:03,788
One person.

1156
01:05:05,806 --> 01:05:08,412
(After hearing his answer, Yeo-min
makes an unreadable expression.)

1157
01:05:08,437 --> 01:05:09,437
What about you?

1158
01:05:10,813 --> 01:05:11,813
Um...

1159
01:05:13,173 --> 01:05:15,602
She asked it, but she's speechless
when she has to answer it.

1160
01:05:15,627 --> 01:05:17,616
- I was flustered.
- I thought you were Nemo.

1161
01:05:17,641 --> 01:05:18,735
I was flustered.

1162
01:05:19,250 --> 01:05:20,711
I don't really know.

1163
01:05:21,643 --> 01:05:23,627
- One... One person?
- One person?

1164
01:05:23,652 --> 01:05:26,105
Give her another option.
You're interested in zero people.

1165
01:05:26,130 --> 01:05:28,242
- 0.8.
- 0.8?

1166
01:05:28,267 --> 01:05:31,800
- You're not sure? I see.
- Someone broke her heart.

1167
01:05:32,115 --> 01:05:33,115
Who is it?

1168
01:05:34,021 --> 01:05:36,124
- He hit bull's eye.
- Someone hurt her.

1169
01:05:36,388 --> 01:05:38,795
- What if that's you?
- It's not me.

1170
01:05:38,994 --> 01:05:40,327
You don't know that.

1171
01:05:40,352 --> 01:05:42,528
Su-won is good at everything
but his own romance.

1172
01:05:45,573 --> 01:05:47,979
- It's not me!
- You could've hurt her.

1173
01:05:48,004 --> 01:05:49,510
- It could be anyone.
- Exactly.

1174
01:05:49,535 --> 01:05:51,506
The perpetrator usually doesn’t know.

1175
01:05:51,531 --> 01:05:52,961
Right. Only the victim knows.

1176
01:05:53,867 --> 01:05:55,060
(Utterly speechless)

1177
01:05:55,085 --> 01:05:56,140
Did you get hurt, Ji-min?

1178
01:05:56,165 --> 01:05:58,427
- But I...
- I mean, it's something similar.

1179
01:05:58,452 --> 01:06:02,676
- I've never even talked with her
before. - You'll really make her cry.

1180
01:06:02,701 --> 01:06:04,416
- Why'd you do that?
- Don't gang up on me.

1181
01:06:04,639 --> 01:06:06,225
And you, stop acting.

1182
01:06:06,682 --> 01:06:08,713
He was really clueless.

1183
01:06:09,480 --> 01:06:11,114
Let's just ask if we have any questions.

1184
01:06:11,139 --> 01:06:13,409
Sure. At this rate, let's just
ask everything we want to.

1185
01:06:14,502 --> 01:06:17,104
Did anyone ask Su-won if
he likes one or two people?

1186
01:06:17,933 --> 01:06:19,199
- No, right?
- No.

1187
01:06:21,072 --> 01:06:25,778
Are you interested in one or
two women in Love Mansion?

1188
01:06:27,333 --> 01:06:29,133
It's a very crucial moment.

1189
01:06:29,531 --> 01:06:30,658
Just say one.

1190
01:06:32,285 --> 01:06:33,820
I think he'll say the wrong thing.

1191
01:06:35,976 --> 01:06:38,690
(What will Su-won say?)

1192
01:06:39,195 --> 01:06:43,361
Two or more.

1193
01:06:43,386 --> 01:06:45,444
- Really?
- Seriously? You're lying.

1194
01:06:45,469 --> 01:06:48,303
- Oh, come on!
- I knew he would say that.

1195
01:06:48,934 --> 01:06:50,000
That's not true.

1196
01:06:50,480 --> 01:06:51,814
Seriously. It's not.

1197
01:06:52,582 --> 01:06:55,423
Then I'll ask Ha-neul.

1198
01:06:55,661 --> 01:06:56,661
Okay.

1199
01:07:00,517 --> 01:07:06,048
Today, until this very moment,

1200
01:07:09,639 --> 01:07:11,139
were you hurt by someone here?

1201
01:07:13,935 --> 01:07:16,516
(No U-turn. They're just
going straight forward?!)

1202
01:07:17,440 --> 01:07:18,440
I can't watch!

1203
01:07:20,991 --> 01:07:22,458
He's asking like that?

1204
01:07:24,852 --> 01:07:27,220
- Yes.
- Yes.

1205
01:07:27,244 --> 01:07:30,419
Yes? I see...

1206
01:07:30,792 --> 01:07:32,192
(Uncomfortable)

1207
01:07:32,560 --> 01:07:36,704
He wanted to know if she was hurt
that he took the coin out of her locker.

1208
01:07:36,729 --> 01:07:38,556
He wanted to know if it affected her.

1209
01:07:40,195 --> 01:07:44,091
- How about Ha-neul asks a question?
- Sure, she can ask away.

1210
01:07:45,334 --> 01:07:48,295
Did you have a change of heart today?

1211
01:07:51,978 --> 01:07:54,438
Rather than that...

1212
01:07:54,985 --> 01:07:59,075
I want to get to know someone else.

1213
01:08:02,513 --> 01:08:09,647
I want to get to know someone else.

1214
01:08:10,784 --> 01:08:13,085
I'll leave it at that.

1215
01:08:13,282 --> 01:08:17,112
You're interested in someone
else, so you want to get to know her?

1216
01:08:17,479 --> 01:08:19,384
Yeah, that's about it.

1217
01:08:20,102 --> 01:08:22,237
Oh no!

1218
01:08:23,889 --> 01:08:25,469
God, I'm doomed!

1219
01:08:25,909 --> 01:08:28,082
(This is awful.)

1220
01:08:30,041 --> 01:08:31,977
I think that's a good enough answer.

1221
01:08:32,998 --> 01:08:35,346
Gosh, don't break her heart.

1222
01:08:35,801 --> 01:08:37,735
Gosh, I shouldn't have drank.

1223
01:08:43,126 --> 01:08:44,816
I think she's gonna cry!

1224
01:08:45,851 --> 01:08:48,446
I really want them to
have a conversation today.

1225
01:08:48,471 --> 01:08:49,965
I want them to talk it out.

1226
01:08:50,476 --> 01:08:52,542
I'm going to ask Ha-neul again.

1227
01:08:53,150 --> 01:08:55,010
Do you just want to talk alone then?

1228
01:08:55,035 --> 01:08:58,234
- Go outside and talk then.
- Why... Why are you doing this?

1229
01:08:58,259 --> 01:09:00,926
Go to the first floor.
Go to the bench.

1230
01:09:01,207 --> 01:09:03,796
- Want to go out? Get some fresh air?
- Go on.

1231
01:09:03,821 --> 01:09:05,954
Yes, go talk amongst yourselves!

1232
01:09:06,334 --> 01:09:08,302
The others have questions, too.

1233
01:09:08,327 --> 01:09:12,304
- The clock is ticking.
- They can't do anything 'cause of you two!

1234
01:09:14,309 --> 01:09:16,309
I hope they can talk honestly.

1235
01:09:21,643 --> 01:09:23,341
Gosh, now she sighs.

1236
01:09:24,258 --> 01:09:26,313
Maybe I shouldn't have asked him that.

1237
01:09:26,338 --> 01:09:28,760
- Why not?
- No, don't say that.

1238
01:09:28,785 --> 01:09:32,961
Because you asked that,
they were able to go and have a talk.

1239
01:09:34,284 --> 01:09:37,133
- She's right.
- What? Are you feeling guilty?

1240
01:09:37,787 --> 01:09:41,247
- They had something to talk about.
- They had to talk.

1241
01:09:42,737 --> 01:09:44,363
- What's wrong?
- It's not your fault.

1242
01:09:44,388 --> 01:09:45,388
(Grab)

1243
01:09:45,534 --> 01:09:47,994
Oh my god! Jung-woo
pulled her towards him! What?

1244
01:09:48,450 --> 01:09:50,537
She was crying, and he
just genuinely pulled her in.

1245
01:09:51,124 --> 01:09:54,341
But look. In-seong went to him right away.

1246
01:09:56,070 --> 01:09:58,799
People who are interested
in each other just can't hide it.

1247
01:09:59,199 --> 01:10:00,445
What's wrong? It's okay.

1248
01:10:00,470 --> 01:10:02,453
They had to talk about it at some point.

1249
01:10:02,772 --> 01:10:04,419
- I'm sorry.
- Don't say that.

1250
01:10:05,074 --> 01:10:07,202
I don't think I'm in my right mind today.

1251
01:10:07,227 --> 01:10:10,903
- It's tough, right?
- Ha-neul just looked so sad.

1252
01:10:11,620 --> 01:10:15,899
- I made the atmosphere weird.
- No, you didn't.

1253
01:10:15,924 --> 01:10:18,124
- No, you didn't.
- Don't worry.

1254
01:10:19,667 --> 01:10:21,500
Now Da-Na isn't happy.

1255
01:10:22,210 --> 01:10:23,750
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I am.

1256
01:10:26,302 --> 01:10:28,842
Why can't they all be at peace?

1257
01:10:31,483 --> 01:10:34,492
(The front of Love Mansion
is filled with silence.)

1258
01:10:42,273 --> 01:10:44,073
Of course I'm sorry to you.

1259
01:10:47,032 --> 01:10:51,270
I'm fine. I'm not really happy
about you apologizing to me.

1260
01:10:53,144 --> 01:10:56,505
I kind of feel humiliated and pathetic...

1261
01:11:00,537 --> 01:11:03,807
If I hadn't been proactive
during the first two days...

1262
01:11:07,282 --> 01:11:10,513
They had an "official couple"
image from the first day.

1263
01:11:13,680 --> 01:11:17,473
Both you and I...

1264
01:11:17,991 --> 01:11:21,224
stole each other's chances...

1265
01:11:22,228 --> 01:11:28,426
You didn't steal my chances. I
went to you because I liked you.

1266
01:11:29,092 --> 01:11:31,838
I know, but since you acted like that,

1267
01:11:32,679 --> 01:11:36,772
the girls who were interested in
you probably couldn't express it.

1268
01:11:36,997 --> 01:11:40,536
And even if there were other guys
interested in me, they couldn't express it.

1269
01:11:42,637 --> 01:11:43,637
I see.

1270
01:11:48,073 --> 01:11:50,120
- No.
- I don't know.

1271
01:11:50,145 --> 01:11:51,947
This is hard. I really have no clue.

1272
01:11:51,972 --> 01:11:53,748
Gosh, I really don't know.

1273
01:11:54,228 --> 01:11:56,688
What will happen to these two?

1274
01:11:57,614 --> 01:12:01,090
I think that at the
end, they'll get back together.

1275
01:12:02,206 --> 01:12:05,428
I think they'll be aware
of each other's feelings.

1276
01:12:05,453 --> 01:12:08,703
- I really don't know how Ahn Ji-min feels.
- Seriously. Me neither.

1277
01:12:08,841 --> 01:12:12,680
Earlier, when he was
talking with Ha-neul, he was

1278
01:12:12,705 --> 01:12:16,772
too busy hearing her
story that he couldn't tell his.

1279
01:12:17,128 --> 01:12:19,128
I'm really curious about that.

1280
01:12:19,153 --> 01:12:20,889
It feels like he lost his chance.

1281
01:12:20,914 --> 01:12:23,829
I'm curious about what
he thinks about Ji-min.

1282
01:12:23,854 --> 01:12:26,213
Earlier, it seemed like
he really had no clue.

1283
01:12:26,478 --> 01:12:29,010
Or he could be a Money
Catcher who's putting on an act.

1284
01:12:29,035 --> 01:12:30,860
Then that'd be really scary!

1285
01:12:30,885 --> 01:12:31,885
That's possible.

1286
01:12:32,096 --> 01:12:37,336
Honestly, ever since the challenges
started, I've been rooting for Won-jae.

1287
01:12:37,419 --> 01:12:42,410
I was about to feel bad that his
feelings for Da-Na were one-sided,

1288
01:12:42,781 --> 01:12:48,545
but she witnessed Jung-woo
pulling In-seong towards him.

1289
01:12:49,010 --> 01:12:51,484
Da-Na is probably
wondering if there's something

1290
01:12:51,509 --> 01:12:54,033
going on between them
that she doesn't know about.

1291
01:12:54,058 --> 01:12:58,611
Then she'll start to wonder if it's right
for her to be interested in Jung-woo.

1292
01:12:59,060 --> 01:13:01,044
Should we choose the answers now?

1293
01:13:01,873 --> 01:13:04,230
I think Jung-woo and
In-seong chose each other.

1294
01:13:04,255 --> 01:13:05,255
Really?

1295
01:13:05,280 --> 01:13:09,114
I felt like he was conscious of
her when they were dancing.

1296
01:13:09,572 --> 01:13:11,436
I'll go with them.

1297
01:13:13,264 --> 01:13:14,264
I choose them.

1298
01:13:14,783 --> 01:13:16,235
- Yeo-min and Jae-hyung?
- Seriously?

1299
01:13:16,260 --> 01:13:18,560
So they connected after
dancing together today?

1300
01:13:19,149 --> 01:13:21,906
(Sunny chose Won-jae and Da-Na.)

1301
01:13:22,282 --> 01:13:24,934
- Really?
- I'm personally rooting for him.

1302
01:13:25,247 --> 01:13:28,556
- But I think it's possible.
- Yeah.

1303
01:13:29,124 --> 01:13:33,441
I think Ji-min and Ji-min
could've chosen each other, too.

1304
01:13:33,954 --> 01:13:39,633
If Ahn Ji-min is a Money Catcher, he'll
go with the one who has eyes for him.

1305
01:13:41,406 --> 01:13:42,606
I'll go with them.

1306
01:13:42,875 --> 01:13:45,232
- Ji-min and Ji-min?
- I just want to root for Yang Ji-min.

1307
01:13:45,598 --> 01:13:46,598
Okay.

1308
01:13:46,798 --> 01:13:48,801
Everyone, the answer is one couple.

1309
01:13:50,501 --> 01:13:52,661
(Did one of them get it right?)

1310
01:13:55,229 --> 01:13:56,793
What's that? What's going on?

1311
01:13:56,818 --> 01:13:58,319
- That scared me.
- What is it?

1312
01:13:58,867 --> 01:13:59,867
I'm curious.

1313
01:13:59,934 --> 01:14:02,719
- Jae-hyung was there!
- Oh, so he was there.

1314
01:14:06,044 --> 01:14:07,044
Oh my god!

1315
01:14:07,069 --> 01:14:10,401
(The winners of the challenge
can go to the Room of Secrets.)

1316
01:14:10,745 --> 01:14:14,278
("Love Catcher in Seoul" Rule - Room
of Secrets: The couple who wins the

1317
01:14:14,303 --> 01:14:17,587
couple challenge can check the secret
of the other in the Room of Secrets.)

1318
01:14:17,612 --> 01:14:19,079
I wonder what's there.

1319
01:14:19,104 --> 01:14:22,176
(What kind of secrets
will they find there?)

1320
01:14:22,201 --> 01:14:25,878
There's a big difference
between going and not going there.

1321
01:14:33,165 --> 01:14:37,050
(They don't know what kind
of secret they'll find out there.)

1322
01:14:37,585 --> 01:14:40,855
They could be curious about
the identity of the one they like.

1323
01:14:41,105 --> 01:14:45,954
Many times, those who go to the Room of
Secrets end up more confused than before.

1324
01:14:46,333 --> 01:14:48,166
What kind of secret is there?

1325
01:14:51,643 --> 01:14:54,307
(Revealing the current love interests)

1326
01:14:55,437 --> 01:14:56,595
This?

1327
01:14:57,017 --> 01:14:59,319
- Oh, this time...
- This is really huge.

1328
01:15:00,045 --> 01:15:01,727
Wow, this is great information.

1329
01:15:01,752 --> 01:15:03,103
It was unexpected.

1330
01:15:03,431 --> 01:15:08,121
I thought I'd be able to pick a
secret about the person I like.

1331
01:15:08,379 --> 01:15:11,308
I seriously had no idea they
would reveal that whole thing.

1332
01:15:11,333 --> 01:15:14,541
They're just revealing
everything this season.

1333
01:15:14,566 --> 01:15:16,274
Yes, I didn't expect it.

1334
01:15:17,030 --> 01:15:19,426
There's going to be a war now.

1335
01:15:19,819 --> 01:15:22,552
- "Now."
- He always makes future plans.

1336
01:15:25,994 --> 01:15:30,604
This is a chance for Money
Catchers to change their plans.

1337
01:15:31,332 --> 01:15:32,681
This is awesome.

1338
01:15:33,191 --> 01:15:34,435
Good luck, Jae-hyung.

1339
01:15:34,748 --> 01:15:36,581
- What is it?
- I'm curious.

1340
01:15:39,042 --> 01:15:42,563
- Okay, Yang Ji-min chose Ahn Ji-min.
- Of course Ji-min chose Ji-min.

1341
01:15:44,076 --> 01:15:46,733
Oh, Yeo-min chose Won-jae!

1342
01:15:46,758 --> 01:15:48,761
She chose him?

1343
01:15:48,786 --> 01:15:52,184
- Wow, this is unexpected.
- I chose an absurd answer.

1344
01:15:56,183 --> 01:15:59,516
- As expected.
- I think they'll end up together.

1345
01:16:01,642 --> 01:16:03,871
Ha-neul chose Su-won.

1346
01:16:04,217 --> 01:16:06,201
- I'm curious about Da-Na.
- Me, too.

1347
01:16:06,561 --> 01:16:08,694
- Is it Jung-woo?
- Or Won-jae?

1348
01:16:09,348 --> 01:16:10,881
- Jung-woo?
- Won-jae?

1349
01:16:13,750 --> 01:16:14,750
Jung-woo.

1350
01:16:15,013 --> 01:16:18,552
- I'm out.
- I have hope.

1351
01:16:23,626 --> 01:16:25,617
Won-jae chose Da-Na.

1352
01:16:27,376 --> 01:16:29,114
I wanted to know who
Jae-hyung would pick.

1353
01:16:31,426 --> 01:16:33,308
- Da-Na?
- It was Da-Na.

1354
01:16:33,333 --> 01:16:35,644
Now it's Ahn Ji-min's turn!

1355
01:16:35,669 --> 01:16:38,050
- This is unpredictable.
- I have a bad feeling...

1356
01:16:38,499 --> 01:16:39,499
Let's do this!

1357
01:16:40,181 --> 01:16:41,181
Ji-min, Ji-min!

1358
01:16:41,835 --> 01:16:43,368
I think it'll be Da-Na.

1359
01:16:46,142 --> 01:16:49,388
I was right! Me! Me! Me!

1360
01:16:51,402 --> 01:16:55,711
- Then I'm the winner!
- Oh, you're right!

1361
01:16:56,213 --> 01:16:57,840
Who did Su-won give his coin to?

1362
01:16:57,865 --> 01:16:59,065
Is it Da-Na again?

1363
01:16:59,360 --> 01:17:00,883
- Really?
- Whoa, no way.

1364
01:17:05,570 --> 01:17:07,645
(Is this real?)

1365
01:17:07,670 --> 01:17:09,077
She almost got all the votes!

1366
01:17:09,102 --> 01:17:11,673
Wow, a truly frightening person has come!

1367
01:17:13,781 --> 01:17:15,360
So only Jung-woo is left.

1368
01:17:16,698 --> 01:17:18,935
Ha-neul talked about
her problems with Da-Na!

1369
01:17:18,960 --> 01:17:19,960
Goodness.

1370
01:17:20,531 --> 01:17:22,939
- Su-won...
- But he chose Da-Na.

1371
01:17:25,070 --> 01:17:26,356
That's mean.

1372
01:17:27,347 --> 01:17:29,938
(Everyone's interests are intertwined.)

1373
01:17:30,608 --> 01:17:33,465
- Then who did Jung-woo pick?
- In-seong.

1374
01:17:35,178 --> 01:17:38,702
Yesterday, he put his
coin in Da-na's locker, right?

1375
01:17:41,763 --> 01:17:42,763
I knew it!

1376
01:17:43,711 --> 01:17:46,363
Take a look! This is how
experienced your senior colleague is!

1377
01:17:47,515 --> 01:17:49,768
(Jung-woo & In-seong)

1378
01:17:49,793 --> 01:17:54,113
I am surprised that I got it right,

1379
01:17:54,138 --> 01:17:58,420
but I had no idea Da-Na would
be chosen by most of the guys.

1380
01:17:58,967 --> 01:18:00,114
That shocked me as well.

1381
01:18:00,139 --> 01:18:03,060
- Doesn't she seem like a Money Catcher?
- I think she's a Love Catcher.

1382
01:18:03,085 --> 01:18:08,779
- Does she seem like a Money Catcher?
- She's friendly to everyone,

1383
01:18:09,095 --> 01:18:10,961
and she looks a bit relaxed.

1384
01:18:12,161 --> 01:18:14,788
That seems like a Money Catcher.

1385
01:18:14,998 --> 01:18:19,045
I think the best twist would be if
Yang Ji-min was a Money Catcher.

1386
01:18:19,645 --> 01:18:24,551
I hope she'll win the money and
confidently march out with her luggage.

1387
01:18:25,127 --> 01:18:28,007
I imagined such a possibility
for our youngest participant.

1388
01:18:30,560 --> 01:18:31,942
- Hello.
- Hey.

1389
01:18:33,517 --> 01:18:36,294
She must have gotten hurt.
Did she hear it?

1390
01:18:40,208 --> 01:18:44,366
I think I'm just watching her from
afar, so I want to try talking to her.

1391
01:18:49,653 --> 01:18:52,534
- Let's go to the first floor.
- The first floor? Sure.

1392
01:18:54,373 --> 01:18:55,729
I don't know what to do.

1393
01:18:56,277 --> 01:18:58,247
Is there someone you want to get to know?

1394
01:18:59,235 --> 01:19:00,957
I think it could change.

1395
01:19:02,139 --> 01:19:03,404
Something popped up.

1396
01:19:03,429 --> 01:19:05,008
(Invite her to your personal space.)

1397
01:19:05,374 --> 01:19:07,948
We have to give the invitation
to them in person? That's hard.

1398
01:19:07,973 --> 01:19:09,984
In my opinion, Su-won
will have the hardest time.

1399
01:19:10,159 --> 01:19:12,278
I was overwhelmed with so many emotions.

1400
01:19:13,210 --> 01:19:14,464
I'm glad you're here.

1401
01:19:14,871 --> 01:19:16,196
I mean it.

1402
01:19:18,676 --> 01:19:20,286
- What's this?
- Something's happening.

1403
01:19:20,311 --> 01:19:21,311
What is it?

1404
01:19:21,336 --> 01:19:23,781
(Tonight, someone will get eliminated.)

1405
01:19:23,806 --> 01:19:25,703
- What the heck?
- This is a lie.

1406
01:19:25,937 --> 01:19:27,095
We never imagined this.

1407
01:19:27,120 --> 01:19:30,869
The one my heart is drawn to is...
I really have no idea.

1408
01:19:32,000 --> 01:19:33,881
I was a bit suspicious of this person.

1409
01:19:34,089 --> 01:19:36,145
All the men seem like Money Catchers.

1410
01:19:36,170 --> 01:19:38,734
I don't have interest in
these five people here.

1411
01:19:38,759 --> 01:19:40,586
(Revealing the Eliminated Members)

1412
01:19:40,611 --> 01:19:42,466
I could end up going home today.

1413
01:19:42,491 --> 01:19:44,018
It could be me.

1414
01:19:44,218 --> 01:19:45,845
Do I need to pack up?

1415
01:19:47,777 --> 01:19:49,143
(Eliminated)

1416
01:19:49,628 --> 01:19:50,628
Really?

1417
01:19:52,687 --> 01:19:54,170
This is seriously a lie.
